main event: A small, silver object was observed maneuvering at high speed over Cynthiana, Kentucky on December 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object was reportedly round in shape and approximately 30 feet in diameter.
The object was observed at an altitude estimated to be 3,000 to 5,000 feet above the ground.
The object was observed for a period of approximately 15 minutes before disappearing from view.
No sound was reported by the witnesses.
Several residents of Cynthiana reported seeing the object.
photographs: no, the report does not mention any photographs
